Subject: [PATCH] Coalesce nil optional bool/string fields to zero values in policy SDK

Speakeasy's RefreshFrom* converters emit types.BoolPointerValue / 
types.StringPointerValue for optional scalar fields. The C1 API omits
zero-valued optional fields on the wire (protobuf), so on refresh these
pointers are nil and the converters write null into state — while the
prior state holds the Go zero value (false / "") that Create/Update
persisted. terraform-plugin-framework then reports a perpetual
false->null (or ""->null) diff on every plan, even with no config change.
Affected ~246 conductorone_policy resources (IGA-1898 / IGA-1899).

This patch rewrites every optional-scalar conversion in the two generated
policy SDK files to the null-coalescing helpers
typeconvert.BoolPointerOrFalse / typeconvert.StringPointerOrEmpty
(internal/provider/typeconvert/pointer.go), which return the zero value
instead of null when the pointer is nil. The helpers live in the
non-generated typeconvert package so they survive regen; this patch
reapplies the call-site swaps that regen would otherwise revert.

Tripwire: TestPolicySDKUsesBoolPointerOrFalse in speakeasy_regen_test.go
fails if a regen reintroduces types.BoolPointerValue in these files.

IGA-1899 (closes IGA-1898 as duplicate — same root cause, same resource).

